{{third-party|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox organization |image = |alt = |caption = IUPS |map = |motto = |formation = {{start date and age|1929}} |extinction = |type = [[International nongovernmental organization|INGO]] |status = |purpose = |headquarters = |language = English |leader_title = President |leader_name = Julie Chan | leader_title3 = Secretary General | leader_name3 = [[Walter Boron]] | leader_name2 = [[Susan Wray]] | leader_title2 = First vice-President |main_organ = |parent_organization = [[International Council for Science]] (ICSU) |affiliations = |budget = |remarks = |name = International Union of Physiological Sciences |image_border = |size = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = IUPS |location = |region_served = Worldwide |membership = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |website = [http://www.iups.org/ IUPS Official website] }}
The '''International Union of Physiological Sciences''', abbreviated IUPS, is the global umbrella organization for [[physiology]].<ref name="About">[http://www.iups.org/about-us/mission-and-vision/ IUPS About Us.]</ref>
IUPS aims to facilitate initiatives that strengthen the discipline of physiology. IUPS is a scientific union member of the [[International Council for Science]] (ICSU),<ref name="Union Member">[http://www.icsu.org/publicdb/frmDisplayMember?docid=73de69c44b92a0427142f457d47bd302 IUPS, International Union of Physiological Sciences. Scientific Union Member.] Retrieved 02 June 2015.</ref> and is accredited with the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO). The Union is composed of 54 National Members, 10 Associate Members, 2 Affiliated Members, 5 Regional Members and 5 Special Members.<ref name="Union Member"/> IUPS organizes an international congress every 4 years and, in association with the [[American Physiological Society]] publishes the review journal [[Physiology (journal)|''Physiology'']].
Since 2010 IUPS takes part in the interdisciplinary activities of ''Bio-Unions/ICSU''.<ref>[http://www.iupesm.org/bio-unionsicsu/ Bio-Unions/ICSU]. Retrieved 02 June 2015.</ref>
