{{update|date=November 2010}} '''Makalaka''' is a general designation used by the [[Bechuana]], [[Northern Ndebele people|Matabele]] and kindred peoples, for conquered or [[Slavery|slave]] [[tribe]]s. Thus, many of the tribes subjugated by the [[Makololo]] chief, [[Sebetwane]] (or Sebituane, or Setitwane) in about 1830 were called Makalaka. The name is more frequently used to designate the [[Makalanga]], one of the tribes now classed as [[Shona people|Mashona]]s, who were brought into subjection by the Matabele.
