'''Mrkojevići''' ([[Montenegrin language|Montenegrin]] and {{lang-sr-cyr|Мркојевићи}}), also known as '''Mrkovići''' (Мрковићи), was a historical tribe in southeastern [[Montenegro]], located between the towns of [[Bar, Montenegro|Bar]] and [[Ulcinj]]. The region covers an area of 91.06&nbsp;km², of which 77.09&nbsp;km² falls in the territory of the Municipality of Bar while 13.97&nbsp;km² falls in the territory of the Municipality of Ulcinj. There are ten main settlements: Velje Selo, Dabezići, Dobra Voda, [[Gorana, Montenegro|Gorana]] (Mala and Velja), Grdovići, Kunje, Ljeskovac, Međureč, Pelinkovići and Pečurice; and three parts: Bušat, Dubrava and Dobra Voda. The region borders [[Krajina, Montenegro|Krajina]] to the east. The majority of inhabitants of the villages identify as [[Montenegrins]], the rest as [[Muslims (nationality)|Muslims]], [[Serbs]] and [[Bosniaks]].
==History== It is believed that the ''[[župa]]'' (county) of [[Prapratna]] was located in what became the Mrkojevići tribe.<ref>{{cite book|title=Srpski dijalektološki zbornik|volume=17-18|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6FzpAAAAMAAJ|year=1968|publisher=Akademija|page=77|quote=ПРЕДГОВОР I. МрковиЬи су )едно од црногорских племена, а живе )ужно од Бара на питомо) и богато) приморено) висоравни за ко)у се лшели да се ту у XI в. налазила жупа Прапратна са при'естоницом зетског кнеза Во)'ислава'.}}</ref> Mrkojevići is first mentioned in 1409.
==Population== According to the 2003 census, the total population of the towns was 3,209.{{citation needed|date=November 2013}}
