'''Penny Hamilton''' (born 1948)<ref name=cogreatwomen/> is a pilot and advocate for women pilots. She has a B.A. from [[Columbia University]] and a Masters and Ph.D. in Community and Human Resources from the [[University of Nebraska]]. She has lived in Granby, [[Colorado]] since 1989. She has a World Aviation Speed Record which she co-holds with her husband.<ref name=stateaviation>{{Cite web|url=http://stateaviationjournal.com/index.php/state-news/colorado/colorado-pilot-wins-lifetime-achievement-award|title=Colorado Pilot Wins Lifetime Achievement Award – State Aviation Journal|website=stateaviationjournal.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-09-03}}</ref> She set it on October 22, 1991. She was inducted into the [[Colorado Aviation Hall of Fame]] in 2011 and was also honored by the Greater Granby Area Chamber of Commerce in 2011 with their Lifetime Achievement Award.<ref name=stateaviation/> In 2012 she received the National Association of State Aviation Officials National Journalism Award.<ref name=cogreatwomen>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cogreatwomen.org/project/penny-hamilton-phd/|title=Penny Hamilton, PhD - Colorado Women's Hall of Fame|work=Colorado Women's Hall of Fame|access-date=2018-09-03|language=en-US}}</ref> She received the ABC-Denver 7 Every Day Hero Award<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://airportjournals.com/colorado-pilot-in-the-news-june-22-2009/|title=Colorado Pilot in the News – June 22, 2009|date=2009-07-01|work=Airport Journals|access-date=2018-09-03|language=en-US}}</ref> for the aviation education programs that she does for children.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.teachingwomentofly.com/penny.htm|title=Teaching Women to Fly - Penny Hamilton Page|website=www.teachingwomentofly.com|access-date=2018-09-03}}</ref> She is also a member of the [[Colorado Aviation Hall of Fame]] and the [[Colorado Women's Hall of Fame]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.skyhinews.com/news/a-living-legend-penny-hamilton-to-be-featured-in-great-colorado-women-series-on-pbs/|title=A living legend: Penny Hamilton to be featured in Great Colorado Women series on PBS|access-date=2018-09-03|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://stateaviationjournal.com/index.php/state-news/colorado/colorado-womens-hall-fame-inducts-penny-hamilton|title=Colorado Women’s Hall of Fame Inducts Penny Hamilton – State Aviation Journal|website=stateaviationjournal.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-09-03}}</ref> She is the director of the Teaching Women to Fly Research Project and also the Colorado Airport History Preservation Project.<ref name=cogreatwomen/>
