The '''RV ''Derinsu''''' is a [[Turkey|Turkish]] [[research vessel|research]] and [[survey vessel]] owned and operated in deep waters by Derinsu Underwater Engineering headquartered in [[Ankara]], Turkey.<ref name="mt"/><ref name="dha1"/><ref name="d"/>
The company operates another research vessel {{RV|Beluga}}.<ref name="dha1"/>
==Vessel== ''Derinsu'' is {{convert|45|m|ftin|abbr=on}} long with a beam of {{convert|15|m|ftin|abbr=on}} and a max. draft of {{convert|4.1|m|ftin|abbr=on}}.<ref name="vf"/> She has a tonnage of {{GT|612}}<ref name="mt"/>
==Research capabilities== Originally a fishing boat, she was refit with state-of-the-art instruments and equipment for [[hydrography|hydrographic]], [[geophysical survey|geophysical]], [[geotechnical engineering|geotechnical]], [[oceanographic survey|oceanographic]] and [[marine environment]]al surveys. The vessel is capable of conducting research work in depths up to {{convert|3000|m|ft|abbr=on}}.<ref name="dha1"/><ref name="ah"/>
==Service== In 2014, she was commissioned to carry out surveys in the [[Black Sea]] off Akliman, [[Sinop, Turkey|Sinop]], where the construction of the [[Sinop Nuclear Power Plant]] is planned. Preliminary research works were completed by the {{RV|TÜBİTAK Marmara}}.<ref name="ah"/>
==See also== *[[List of research vessels by country#Turkey|List of research vessels of Turkey]] * {{RV|Beluga}}
