'''Federal Radio Corporation of Nigeria Kaduna''', formerly known as '''Radio Kaduna''', was founded in 1962. It now has the largest radio listenership in [[sub-Saharan Africa]].
The station broadcasts in Hausa English, Nupe and Kanuri. The Hausa programme can be heard in Kaduna state and worldwide on 6090 kHz shortwave, and the English programme on 4770 kHz. FM channels in Kaduna city are Supreme FM on 96.1 MHz and Karama FM on 92.1 MHz.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ww2.radionigeria.gov.ng/fr360.php?360ID=9 |title=Radio Nigeria Online |publisher=Federal Radio Corporation of Nigeria |date= |accessdate=2010-08-18}}</ref>
