{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Grodno |latin = Dioecesis Grodnensis |local = Гродзенскай дыяцэзіі |image = Гродно Костел Фарный 01.jpg |image_size = 300px |caption = [[St. Francis Xavier Cathedral, Grodno|Cathedral Basilica of St Francis Xavier]] |country = {{flag|Belarus}} |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Minsk-Mohilev|Minsk-Mohilev]] |province = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Minsk-Mohilev|Minsk-Mohilev]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |cathedral = св. Францішка Ксаверыя (''[[St. Francis Xavier Cathedral, Grodno|Cathedral Basilica of St. Francis Xavier]]'') |cocathedral = |area_km2 = 25,000 |population = 1,058,346 |population_as_of = 2013 |catholics = 582,540 |catholics_percent= 55 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Aleksander Kaszkiewicz]] |metro_archbishop = [[Tadeusz Kondrusiewicz (bishop)|Tadeusz Kondrusiewicz]] |coadjutor = |auxiliary_bishops= |emeritus_bishops = |map = BelarusHrodnaDiocese.png |map_caption = Location of Diocese of Grodno in Belarus |website = [http://grodnensis.by Website of the Diocese] }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Grodno''' ({{lang-la|Grodnen(sis) Latinorum}}, {{lang-be|Гродзенская дыяцэзія}}) is an [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Hrodna]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Minsk-Mohilev|Minsk-Mohilev]] in Belarus.
==History== * 13 April 1991: Established as Diocese of Grodno
==Leadership== * [[Bishop]]s of Grodno (Roman rite) ** [[Aleksander Kaszkiewicz]] (Аляксандр Кашкевіч) (since 13 Apr 1991)
==See also== *[[Roman Catholicism in Belarus]] *[[List of Roman Catholic dioceses in Belarus]]
==Sources== * [http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/grod0.htm GCatholic.org] * [http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dgrod.html Catholic Hierarchy]
